01:26.545 --> 01:28.002
OFJOSEPH: <i>Heresy.</i>

01:28.297 --> 01:30.084
<i>That's what they're
hanging for.</i>

01:31.216 --> 01:34.050
<i>Not for being part of the resistance
because, officially,</i>

01:34.469 --> 01:36.131
<i>there is no resistance.</i>

01:37.014 --> 01:40.052
<i>Not for helping people escape
because, officially,</i>

01:40.350 --> 01:42.262
<i>there is
no such thing as escape.</i>

01:43.812 --> 01:46.896
<i>They hang for being heretics,
not martyrs.</i>

01:48.025 --> 01:49.766
<i>Martyrs inspire.</i>

01:50.611 --> 01:52.193
<i>Heretics are just stupid.</i>

01:52.279 --> 01:53.815
(SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)

01:53.905 --> 01:55.897
<i>Was I being stupid?</i>

02:01.121 --> 02:02.612
(WIND HOWLING)

02:05.584 --> 02:07.450
<i>I don't think Cora's up there.</i>

02:07.836 --> 02:09.919
<i>I don't think
Lawrence would do that.</i>

02:13.091 --> 02:14.673
OFJOSEPH: Do you
recognize anybody?

02:15.469 --> 02:17.256
ALMA: It's impossible
to tell.

02:18.513 --> 02:20.220
They're starting
to smell.

02:20.766 --> 02:22.883
Looks like the same batch
from yesterday.

02:23.060 --> 02:24.426
And the day before.

02:25.562 --> 02:26.894
Maybe they're done.

02:27.522 --> 02:28.683
With Marthas.

02:29.733 --> 02:30.733
Who's next?

02:30.901 --> 02:32.312
GUARDIAN: No talking!

02:32.778 --> 02:34.735
And, you, go join
your walking partner.

02:36.782 --> 02:38.489
OFJOSEPH: <i>If I'm going
to survive this,</i>

02:38.659 --> 02:39.820
<i>I'll need allies.</i>

02:41.912 --> 02:43.369
<i>Allies with power.</i>

02:43.872 --> 02:44.872
(DOOR CLOSES)

03:04.893 --> 03:07.135
OFJOSEPH: <i>To be a man
watched by women,</i>

03:07.979 --> 03:09.845
<i>it must be entirely strange.</i>

03:11.566 --> 03:13.853
<i>To have them watching him
all the time.</i>

03:16.029 --> 03:17.861
<i>To have them flinch
when he moves.</i>

03:19.408 --> 03:22.697
<i>To have them wondering,
"What is he going to do next?</i>

03:24.579 --> 03:25.945
<i>"Does he like me?</i>

03:27.249 --> 03:28.410
<i>"Will he keep me?</i>

03:29.251 --> 03:30.412
<i>"Am I safe here?"</i>

03:36.550 --> 03:38.041
<i>Cora wasn't.</i>

03:38.135 --> 03:39.421
Blessed be the fruit.

03:41.513 --> 03:42.845
May the Lord open.

03:45.434 --> 03:47.676
- Got the groceries. Anything else I can do?
- I got it.

03:50.522 --> 03:53.230
(SIGHS) Could you plate
the pastries, please?

03:53.650 --> 03:54.650
No problem.

03:56.236 --> 03:57.477
Why are
they coming here?

03:57.612 --> 03:58.853
I don't know.

03:59.197 --> 04:01.405
My old Commander said
Lawrence won't go to meetings.

04:02.075 --> 04:03.995
They want to talk to him,
they have to come here.

04:05.036 --> 04:06.152
That's how powerful he is.

04:06.705 --> 04:08.196
- Hmm.
- Thanks for the insight.

04:10.709 --> 04:12.166
- (SPILLING)
- LAWRENCE: Oh!

04:12.252 --> 04:13.618
Sienna!

04:15.922 --> 04:17.163
Sienna!

04:17.632 --> 04:18.839
(BETH SIGHS)

04:19.259 --> 04:20.259
Go.

04:29.728 --> 04:31.014
I went to the square.

04:31.104 --> 04:32.515
I don't think
Cora's up there.

04:33.815 --> 04:36.353
(SIGHS) So, she's on a bus
to The Colonies?

04:38.904 --> 04:40.770
Have you been getting
any messages at all?

04:43.283 --> 04:44.524
Anyone who knows anything

04:44.618 --> 04:46.359
is probably
up on those gallows.

04:48.497 --> 04:49.738
LAWRENCE: Beth, refill.

04:49.956 --> 04:50.956
Coming.

04:52.334 --> 04:54.075
(SIGHS) He's testing us.

04:55.629 --> 04:56.995
We're all disposable.

05:12.479 --> 05:14.516
Are Marthas supposed
to be clean?

05:18.860 --> 05:22.319
Would you consider that
a basic criteria for the job?

05:26.701 --> 05:28.283
(WHIMPERING)

05:35.085 --> 05:36.701
(DOORBELL RINGING)

05:41.299 --> 05:43.712
Can I get the door
for you, sir?

05:44.094 --> 05:45.505
I don't know. Are you

05:47.138 --> 05:49.095
capable of
solving problems?

05:49.182 --> 05:52.016
Of making decisions?

05:55.188 --> 05:56.975
Do you know
what the penalty is?

05:59.734 --> 06:02.727
For Handmaids
who open front doors?

06:05.782 --> 06:08.616
I'm actually asking.
I don't know.

06:11.621 --> 06:13.783
What do you think
the penalty should be?

06:16.167 --> 06:17.328
What would be fair?

06:26.219 --> 06:28.085
Forget it. Forget it.

06:32.517 --> 06:34.725
I guess you're not capable.

06:35.061 --> 06:36.302
(LAWRENCE SIGHS)

06:41.484 --> 06:43.976
(MEN CHATTERING)

06:44.070 --> 06:47.529
WARREN: The shipment of females
from Chicago arrived yesterday.

06:47.616 --> 06:49.983
Well, we have needs
in the agricultural Colonies.

06:50.076 --> 06:52.068
They're not worthy
of The Colonies.

06:52.537 --> 06:54.745
LAWRENCE: I'm looking at

06:54.831 --> 06:59.166
a utility maximization framework
with a deteriorating labor supply.

06:59.252 --> 07:00.252
I need workers.

07:00.629 --> 07:02.541
(MEN CHATTERING)

07:07.928 --> 07:09.169
Blessed be the fruit.

07:12.182 --> 07:13.889
May the Lord open.

07:14.392 --> 07:16.384
I hope you and
Mrs. Waterford are well.

07:18.939 --> 07:20.271
Do you?

07:22.609 --> 07:24.191
Is Serena okay?

07:24.277 --> 07:28.191
Well, after what you put
us through, I'm not sure.

07:28.740 --> 07:29.740
She's tough.

07:31.534 --> 07:32.866
She'll be okay.

07:38.667 --> 07:40.954
So, how is your

07:41.670 --> 07:43.627
new house treating you?

07:43.838 --> 07:48.549
I pray that God will make me
worthy of my new Commander.

07:48.885 --> 07:51.673
Oh, I'm sure
you'll prove yourself.

07:53.139 --> 07:55.096
OFJOSEPH: What do you
know about him?

07:56.184 --> 07:58.892
He's an interesting man.

08:00.772 --> 08:04.766
Instrumental in Gilead's
creation. Our visionary.

08:06.903 --> 08:08.860
Mmm. What else?

08:10.323 --> 08:11.323
(COMMANDER FRED SCOFFS)

08:12.659 --> 08:15.367
We've always found him
a bit hard to read.

08:17.497 --> 08:20.205
Well, if you can't read him,
I don't know who can.

08:22.752 --> 08:24.744
Lawrence is a survivor.

08:24.963 --> 08:26.545
Aren't we all, sir?

08:27.048 --> 08:30.086
He is particularly
well suited to it.

08:32.761 --> 08:34.970
He's not sentimental,
not like me.

08:37.017 --> 08:39.509
I never found you

08:39.894 --> 08:42.385
overly sentimental, sir.

08:46.901 --> 08:48.267
You were merciful.

08:51.197 --> 08:53.280
You know,
after everything...

08:54.034 --> 08:55.696
I'm still alive.

09:00.123 --> 09:02.991
I will always be grateful
to you for that.

09:05.712 --> 09:07.954
But I am not
in your house anymore.

09:10.633 --> 09:12.465
I need you to tell me

09:13.053 --> 09:15.887
anything about Lawrence
that you think could help me.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.722
He does not like
to be bored.

09:23.271 --> 09:25.308
(LAWRENCE CLEARS THROAT)

09:26.107 --> 09:28.815
But I guess you
knew that already.

09:31.905 --> 09:33.692
Blessed day,
Commander Lawrence.

09:33.782 --> 09:35.694
It's a privilege to be
in your home again.

09:36.493 --> 09:39.486
Yeah, I always
hated commuting.

09:41.790 --> 09:43.656
You two know each other.

09:44.667 --> 09:46.829
Oh, yes.

09:47.170 --> 09:50.834
You used to be Offred.

09:52.383 --> 09:53.749
Do you miss it?

09:55.220 --> 09:58.088
COMMANDER FRED:
Well, she's Ofjoseph now.

09:59.265 --> 10:01.131
I should let you go.

10:01.392 --> 10:03.384
- Under His eye.
- Sure.

10:08.274 --> 10:09.560
LAWRENCE: You working hard?

10:16.783 --> 10:18.024
Yes.

10:19.202 --> 10:20.568
At what?

10:25.416 --> 10:26.952
You don't have
to answer that.

10:55.321 --> 10:58.280
- SERENA: I'm not cold, Mom.
- PAMELA: Oh, yes, you are.

11:04.539 --> 11:07.122
Our prayer circle's
coming to the house today.

11:08.459 --> 11:09.459
(SIGHS)

11:09.544 --> 11:12.412
- I'll try and stay out of your way.
- No.

11:12.589 --> 11:14.922
No, they all want
to see you.

11:15.884 --> 11:17.125
What an honor
for them.

11:18.887 --> 11:20.767
I don't want to hang out
with your friends, Mom.

11:20.847 --> 11:23.055
You're an excellent
conversationalist.

11:24.017 --> 11:25.428
It wouldn't be
a real visit

11:25.518 --> 11:27.100
if I didn't get
to show you off.

11:29.314 --> 11:31.306
I don't have any clothes.

11:33.902 --> 11:36.485
Mrs. Manning gave us
a dress that she's outgrown.

11:39.032 --> 11:40.318
I think it will fit.

11:51.753 --> 11:53.619
SERENA: This won't
be too bad.

11:54.255 --> 11:56.247
I'm gonna
take it up a bit.

11:57.258 --> 11:59.420
- Fix that neckline.
- (KNOCKING ON DOOR)

12:01.429 --> 12:04.172
(GASPS) There you are.

12:05.767 --> 12:07.008
Praise be.

12:19.197 --> 12:20.984
You look beautiful.

12:27.038 --> 12:29.878
SIENNA: Lawrence wants you pouring
the Commanders' drinks instead of me.

12:34.087 --> 12:35.294
Why?

12:36.547 --> 12:38.334
He said I wasn't
pouring fast enough.

12:46.391 --> 12:48.098
CALHOUN:
Pages ten through 16,

12:48.184 --> 12:51.518
detail the expansion of
our training facility in Fort Stevens.

12:51.938 --> 12:54.646
WARREN: To support
the troop surge in Chicago.

12:55.108 --> 12:57.270
CALHOUN:
Phase one of the surge.

12:57.694 --> 13:00.653
We need to prepare ourselves
for more troop deployments down the line.

13:00.738 --> 13:02.400
WARREN:
One last measured push,

13:02.490 --> 13:05.824
and Chicago should roll up the last of
the insurgent strongholds, no?

13:05.910 --> 13:07.446
CALHOUN:
The insurgency's contagious.

13:07.578 --> 13:10.616
We need to look at starting a steady,
sustained bombing campaign.

13:10.748 --> 13:13.582
No, there is value
to be mined there.

13:14.002 --> 13:16.665
Children, fertile women.
Move on to the next.

13:18.548 --> 13:21.336
On page 17,
you'll see a timeline

13:22.135 --> 13:25.845
depicting a series of district-wide Salvagings
beginning next week.

13:26.139 --> 13:28.819
COMMANDER FRED: I thought we discussed
sending them to The Colonies?

13:28.850 --> 13:30.411
CALHOUN: The Colonies are
a slap on the wrist.

13:30.435 --> 13:31.596
WARREN:
They are merely women.

13:31.769 --> 13:33.977
CALHOUN: Women under
the sway of terrorists.

13:34.647 --> 13:37.765
We don't want our own women
becoming restless, do we?

13:40.028 --> 13:42.361
Salvagings are an effective
tool of instruction.

13:42.655 --> 13:44.362
It's been too long
since the last one.

13:45.366 --> 13:49.235
We know women can inflate
their abilities

13:50.038 --> 13:53.281
and think they belong
in places they don't.

13:54.250 --> 13:56.458
But they can also
be put to use.

13:58.254 --> 14:00.416
- And they can be fun.
- (MEN LAUGHING)

14:00.757 --> 14:02.168
Ofjoseph?

14:04.260 --> 14:09.255
We're puzzling out
how to assess

14:09.766 --> 14:15.387
an individual's value in the world
as it pertains to gender.

14:16.356 --> 14:18.848
Weren't you a book editor,
once upon a time?

14:20.860 --> 14:21.860
Yes, sir.

14:24.322 --> 14:26.109
Are there any books
on the topic?

14:26.282 --> 14:27.989
Yes, sir.

14:28.493 --> 14:29.493
Many.

14:29.577 --> 14:32.786
LAWRENCE: <i>Sex Differences
in Cognitive Abilities.</i>

14:33.373 --> 14:34.830
<i>The Descent of Man.</i>

14:35.583 --> 14:38.667
An oldie but a goodie. That's...
That's what you were thinking of, right?

14:38.753 --> 14:40.790
I think I have it
here somewhere.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.418
Uh, would you
get it for me?

14:44.509 --> 14:47.377
It's on top of the bookcase
to the right of the door.

15:14.080 --> 15:17.573
LAWRENCE: Oh, the stack
on the left.

15:17.959 --> 15:19.120
Third book down.

15:19.752 --> 15:20.833
Yellow lettering.

15:32.140 --> 15:33.140
Good job.

16:00.168 --> 16:02.501
Is there anything else
I can help you with, sir?

16:03.004 --> 16:04.004
LAWRENCE: No, I'm good.

16:06.340 --> 16:07.340
You're done.

16:21.147 --> 16:22.558
See? Women can be useful.

16:22.899 --> 16:24.310
(MEN LAUGHING)

17:02.271 --> 17:03.271
(SEAGULLS SQUAWKING)

17:07.568 --> 17:08.568
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

17:11.614 --> 17:13.320
RITA: Your mother has
a lot of friends.

17:15.201 --> 17:17.488
SERENA: She's an excellent
conversationalist.

17:21.040 --> 17:22.406
RITA: I made
something for you.

17:49.026 --> 17:50.062
Here.

17:50.152 --> 17:51.152
(CLEARS THROAT)

18:05.710 --> 18:07.417
You will get
through this, ma'am.

18:08.713 --> 18:09.954
By His hand.

18:11.132 --> 18:12.293
What's left of it.

18:19.515 --> 18:21.051
DANIEL: Though
the Earth give way,

18:21.350 --> 18:23.182
though the mountains
fall into the sea...

18:23.644 --> 18:25.761
ALL: God is
our refuge and strength.

18:26.272 --> 18:29.481
DANIEL: Dear Lord,
please heal my wife.

18:30.776 --> 18:33.769
For my beloved is mine
and I am hers.

18:34.322 --> 18:36.359
ALL: God is
our refuge and strength.

18:36.449 --> 18:38.657
DANIEL: And the Lord shall
guide thee continually

18:38.993 --> 18:41.451
and satisfy thy soul
in drought.

18:42.163 --> 18:43.529
Make fat thy bones.

18:43.914 --> 18:45.997
ALL: Show us
Thy mercy, O Lord.

18:48.419 --> 18:50.285
DANIEL: Thank you
for your prayers.

18:51.797 --> 18:53.789
Is anyone else
in need of comfort?

18:57.803 --> 18:58.884
Serena?

19:19.617 --> 19:23.201
Dear Lord, Serena Joy
has suffered a great loss.

19:23.704 --> 19:26.321
Please give her relief
from her distress.

19:26.582 --> 19:29.450
Be merciful to her
and hear her prayers.

19:29.669 --> 19:31.706
The Lord is close
to the brokenhearted.

19:31.796 --> 19:34.209
ALL: He rescues those whose spirits
are crushed.

19:34.423 --> 19:36.130
DANIEL: Psalm 6:2, please.

19:41.972 --> 19:43.713
Be merciful, O Lord,

19:44.684 --> 19:45.925
for I am faint.

19:51.524 --> 19:55.609
Heal me, O Lord,
for my soul is in anguish.

19:58.781 --> 19:59.942
DANIEL: Dear Lord, we pray

20:00.032 --> 20:01.864
for the safe return
of Serena's child.

20:02.868 --> 20:05.110
And we pray
for her marriage to heal.

20:05.746 --> 20:07.612
ALL: For love
is strong as death.

20:07.707 --> 20:09.164
DANIEL: Wives,
submit yourselves

20:09.250 --> 20:11.492
unto your own husbands,
as unto the Lord.

20:11.669 --> 20:13.535
ALL: For the husband
is the head of the wife.

20:13.629 --> 20:15.916
DANIEL: Even as Christ
is the head of the church,

20:16.006 --> 20:17.542
so let the Wives be

20:17.633 --> 20:19.420
to their own husbands
in everything.

20:19.510 --> 20:20.796
ALL: Let every wife

20:20.886 --> 20:22.843
see that she revere
her husband.

20:23.347 --> 20:25.304
This is the word
of the Lord.

20:36.485 --> 20:37.963
COMMANDER FRED:
When we first were married,

20:37.987 --> 20:41.230
I'd come home and open
the door but just a crack.

20:42.074 --> 20:43.074
I'd wait.

20:44.285 --> 20:46.447
I'd listen
for your footsteps.

20:47.288 --> 20:48.288
(CHUCKLES)

20:48.914 --> 20:50.906
I'd push open the door
a little more.

20:53.961 --> 20:55.918
I'd get a glimpse
of your hair,

20:57.965 --> 20:59.501
long and loose.

21:00.676 --> 21:01.792
(CHUCKLES)

21:03.137 --> 21:06.175
I'd dole out to myself

21:06.265 --> 21:09.224
little helpings of you,
like a kid with dessert.

21:14.356 --> 21:15.972
The kind of man
I had become.

21:16.567 --> 21:19.105
Married to
a woman like you.

21:19.195 --> 21:20.902
Coming home to you.

21:27.703 --> 21:29.319
Other men, I

21:30.456 --> 21:31.456
(SIGHS)

21:32.374 --> 21:33.410
felt sorry for.

21:33.501 --> 21:37.290
They had nothing to work for,
nothing to fight for.

21:37.379 --> 21:41.123
They didn't
get to have you.

21:46.430 --> 21:47.921
A Commander is

21:50.059 --> 21:53.097
the head of the household.
The house is

21:54.730 --> 21:55.937
what he holds.

21:57.566 --> 22:00.604
To have and to hold,
till death do us part.

22:02.863 --> 22:07.654
I may not be
a perfect man but I

22:10.496 --> 22:12.988
will try to be better.

22:21.423 --> 22:22.584
If I lose you,

22:25.302 --> 22:26.588
I lose everything.

22:28.180 --> 22:29.512
JEZEBEL: That sounds good.

22:30.724 --> 22:32.244
Would you like to
run through it again?

22:38.065 --> 22:39.556
OFJOSEPH: <i>I compose myself.</i>

22:41.318 --> 22:43.981
<i>My self is a thing
I must now compose</i>

22:44.363 --> 22:46.446
<i>as one composes a speech.</i>

22:51.370 --> 22:53.202
<i>I'm not proud
of myself for this.</i>

22:53.789 --> 22:54.996
<i>Or for any of it.</i>

22:56.458 --> 22:57.458
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

23:00.212 --> 23:01.212
LAWRENCE: What?

23:12.558 --> 23:13.558
(DOOR CLOSES)

23:15.019 --> 23:18.012
LAWRENCE: You think an accountant
could make a good cook? (SIGHS)

23:20.274 --> 23:21.274
Yes, sir.

23:21.901 --> 23:22.901
(SIGHS)

23:24.486 --> 23:26.102
Binders full of women.

23:26.780 --> 23:28.521
I thought you might
like some tea.

23:30.075 --> 23:31.075
LAWRENCE: Thanks.

23:32.286 --> 23:33.286
Long day?

23:34.204 --> 23:36.241
My work
is just beginning.

23:36.332 --> 23:37.948
At least the people
are gone.

23:39.043 --> 23:40.043
(LAWRENCE SIGHS)

23:40.127 --> 23:41.868
OFJOSEPH: It's tiring
having people around.

23:41.962 --> 23:42.962
(TEA POURING)

23:50.346 --> 23:53.805
Does it seem like that would
be particularly difficult

23:53.891 --> 23:55.473
for someone like me?

23:56.310 --> 23:59.474
Oh, I don't really know
what you're like, sir.

24:02.691 --> 24:05.434
Do you consider yourself good
at managing people?

24:09.281 --> 24:11.819
Not particularly, no.

24:13.827 --> 24:15.864
You seem like you'd be good
at making friends.

24:17.706 --> 24:19.493
Good at influencing people.

24:22.920 --> 24:24.456
Good at intimacy.

24:30.135 --> 24:31.135
Thank you.

24:41.146 --> 24:43.479
Did this really
work on Fred?

24:44.525 --> 24:45.525
(LAWRENCE CHUCKLES)

24:46.068 --> 24:48.651
Not exactly
an intellectual giant.

24:48.821 --> 24:51.484
But, then again,
neither are you.

24:52.992 --> 24:54.073
(LAWRENCE SIGHS)

24:54.493 --> 24:58.407
Perhaps you don't know me
well enough yet, sir.

24:59.748 --> 25:01.034
Here's what I don't get.

25:01.750 --> 25:05.243
If women don't want
to be defined by their bodies,

25:05.504 --> 25:07.996
why are they always using them
to get what they want?

25:08.090 --> 25:09.251
Maybe they aren't.

25:09.800 --> 25:12.087
Maybe men are just
too easily distracted.

25:17.850 --> 25:21.514
Speaking of the Waterfords, you really
mucked up that house, didn't you?

25:22.229 --> 25:27.270
Had Fred demoted, Serena defingered,
baby baby-napped.

25:28.819 --> 25:32.483
You left the place
literally in ashes.

25:33.741 --> 25:35.858
Do you think they got
what they deserved?

25:36.201 --> 25:38.784
No one in Gilead gets
what they deserve, sir.

25:39.538 --> 25:43.953
How could they not realize
how transactional you are?

25:44.043 --> 25:45.454
I did what I had to do.

25:46.128 --> 25:48.128
You think if you get me
to like you, I'll help you?

25:49.214 --> 25:51.706
I think that you might try.

25:54.011 --> 25:56.094
I think you might try
to do the right thing.

25:58.849 --> 26:00.636
What do you know
about the right thing?

26:00.726 --> 26:02.968
I know you helped Emily
escape with that baby.

26:04.313 --> 26:08.057
And I know you let the Marthas run
a resistance network out of your house.

26:09.276 --> 26:12.815
You have to let the rabble-rousers
blow off a little steam,

26:12.905 --> 26:15.192
or they'll smash
everything to bits.

26:18.494 --> 26:21.578
Do you want to know
why I helped Emily?

26:21.830 --> 26:23.241
I think you felt guilty.

26:24.708 --> 26:26.074
I think you felt
sorry for her.

26:26.168 --> 26:28.205
You want me to feel guilty
and sorry for you?

26:28.295 --> 26:29.376
Do you?

26:35.010 --> 26:36.501
I helped Emily

26:38.597 --> 26:41.340
because she
is unnaturally smart

26:42.226 --> 26:46.391
and could be useful
to the world one day.

26:47.231 --> 26:49.393
If you were smart, you would
have gotten on that truck.

26:49.483 --> 26:50.849
You know why
I couldn't.

26:50.943 --> 26:53.560
I think I care more about
your daughter than you do.

26:54.613 --> 26:56.570
I'm saving
the planet for her.

26:56.949 --> 27:01.694
I'm replenishing
the human race for her.

27:01.787 --> 27:02.787
What are you doing?

27:02.871 --> 27:04.612
I am trying
to be her mother!

27:04.706 --> 27:05.947
She has a mother.

27:06.458 --> 27:08.074
You met Mrs. Mackenzie.

27:08.252 --> 27:11.871
She's a lovely woman.
She never stole anybody's husband.

27:12.214 --> 27:15.457
Do you know that she organized
1,000 food baskets

27:15.551 --> 27:18.089
for orphans in Africa back
when there were orphans?

27:18.178 --> 27:20.170
What did you ever do
to help anyone?

27:20.973 --> 27:23.932
Except edit esoteric,
useless books

27:24.017 --> 27:25.883
that no one
was ever gonna read

27:25.978 --> 27:30.097
instead of picking up
your sick daughter from school.

27:37.614 --> 27:38.614
Useless.

27:49.376 --> 27:51.663
You wrote esoteric books.

27:53.255 --> 27:54.496
You did that.

27:57.509 --> 28:03.506
God, it must be
scary, huh?

28:03.807 --> 28:07.221
Seeing the numbers on those spreadsheets
turn into real people?

28:07.311 --> 28:09.223
Real people
being executed?

28:10.063 --> 28:15.400
Knowing that if no one had read your books,
we would all be better off.

28:15.485 --> 28:18.353
It must be hell
being a man like that.

28:19.740 --> 28:21.902
Far worse than useless.

28:23.535 --> 28:25.242
You know what?
I get it.

28:25.746 --> 28:28.454
I get why
you would do this.

28:28.540 --> 28:31.578
I suppose you would hole yourself up
in a house like this,

28:31.835 --> 28:33.622
playing games
with people's heads,

28:33.712 --> 28:36.420
doing a good deed or two
every once in a while,

28:36.506 --> 28:38.668
so that you can
fucking sleep at night.

28:50.938 --> 28:52.804
How tempting it is to

28:55.734 --> 28:58.147
invent a humanity

29:02.449 --> 29:03.940
for anyone at all.

29:12.209 --> 29:13.209
Come on.

29:19.967 --> 29:21.253
Let's take a drive.

29:39.027 --> 29:41.235
(MAN CHATTERING OVER RADIO)

29:46.201 --> 29:47.201
(CLANGING)

30:00.924 --> 30:01.924
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

30:26.867 --> 30:28.859
(WOMEN COUGHING)

30:44.968 --> 30:48.132
There will be no Salvagings.

30:49.765 --> 30:52.257
They're bound for
The Colonies tomorrow.

30:53.018 --> 30:54.259
(MAN CHATTERING OVER RADIO)

30:55.771 --> 30:57.228
So they'll die anyways?

30:57.397 --> 30:59.138
LAWRENCE: All save five.

30:59.649 --> 31:04.940
I was able to requisition five
to serve as Marthas.

31:06.823 --> 31:07.823
Good for you.

31:08.408 --> 31:09.990
Five is better than none.

31:10.077 --> 31:11.318
Make them all Marthas.

31:11.411 --> 31:13.073
We only have
five openings.

31:25.050 --> 31:26.416
(WOMAN COUGHING)

31:26.927 --> 31:28.338
You get to choose

31:29.846 --> 31:31.303
who is worthy

31:31.390 --> 31:33.256
of becoming a Martha.

31:39.689 --> 31:41.250
You'll have all
the information you need.

31:41.274 --> 31:43.482
Names, ages, occupations,

31:43.568 --> 31:46.936
academic attainments,
moral stains.

31:48.657 --> 31:49.738
That's dumb.

31:51.576 --> 31:54.410
Who gets to define morality?

31:55.705 --> 31:57.412
Just choose the best people
for the job.

31:58.125 --> 31:59.332
(COUGHING CONTINUES)

31:59.418 --> 32:00.829
(MAN CHATTERING OVER RADIO)

32:03.004 --> 32:04.085
No.

32:04.172 --> 32:08.132
I thought you might enjoy
being useful, for once.

32:10.595 --> 32:12.177
None of them
deserves to die.

32:14.015 --> 32:16.382
What if I told you,
if you don't choose, they all die?

32:25.318 --> 32:28.311
I am not responsible
for their deaths.

32:28.405 --> 32:30.647
You are. Gilead is.

32:31.450 --> 32:33.237
A technical distinction

32:33.660 --> 32:35.652
that won't mean anything
to these women.

32:36.288 --> 32:37.904
But I can see
it's important to you.

32:40.000 --> 32:42.160
And that's more important
than anything else, isn't it?

32:45.046 --> 32:46.503
I'm not doing it.

32:50.385 --> 32:51.501
I won't.

32:56.766 --> 32:57.802
LAWRENCE: Close it.

32:57.893 --> 32:59.009
(SOBBING)

33:17.037 --> 33:18.448
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

33:31.176 --> 33:34.089
PAMELA: Oh, you're all wet.

33:34.721 --> 33:37.555
You've gotten too used to
the mild climate in the city.

33:38.600 --> 33:41.308
She's forgotten how we must battle
the elements out here.

33:41.811 --> 33:44.053
Why don't you go upstairs,
dear, change?

33:44.189 --> 33:46.522
- I'm fine.
- You need to get out of those wet things.

33:46.816 --> 33:47.932
No, I'm fine.

33:48.026 --> 33:50.643
PAMELA: Let Clara fix you
some warm pumpkin soup.

33:51.363 --> 33:53.070
Clara, can you please
excuse us?

34:01.790 --> 34:04.578
I really wish that you hadn't invited
those people over.

34:04.668 --> 34:05.875
I'm sorry, dear.

34:05.961 --> 34:08.498
You told them everything about me
and about my marriage.

34:08.588 --> 34:11.422
You're right.
I shouldn't have done that.

34:11.716 --> 34:12.922
SERENA:
Why did you do it?

34:14.010 --> 34:16.377
Now that I know,
I won't do it again.

34:19.808 --> 34:21.344
What can I make
you to eat, dear?

34:22.018 --> 34:23.259
SERENA: Stop it!

34:24.688 --> 34:26.554
You want me to
go back to Fred.

34:27.649 --> 34:29.139
PAMELA: I only want
you to be happy.

34:30.485 --> 34:33.193
- I need you to know what it was like between us...
- No.

34:34.197 --> 34:35.556
SERENA: And the things
that we did.

34:35.824 --> 34:36.940
Those things are private.

34:37.033 --> 34:38.469
That's because you
don't want to know.

34:38.493 --> 34:40.405
Because none
of it matters.

34:46.042 --> 34:47.042
Look at you,

34:49.045 --> 34:50.877
all the gifts
you've been given.

34:52.007 --> 34:55.876
But you need everything
to be exactly how you want.

34:57.304 --> 34:58.545
A spoiled little girl.

35:05.604 --> 35:06.685
I'm sorry.

35:09.274 --> 35:11.982
You know there's no place
in this world for you without Fred.

35:16.823 --> 35:18.314
(CRYING)

35:31.379 --> 35:34.372
You need to take a deep breath
and see things.

35:35.091 --> 35:36.423
You're a beautiful woman.

35:37.135 --> 35:38.135
And Fred,

35:38.219 --> 35:41.587
you and Fred together,
the Waterfords?

35:42.182 --> 35:43.218
(CHUCKLES)

35:44.267 --> 35:45.383
What a fine couple.

35:45.477 --> 35:47.389
That doesn't mean anything.

35:47.479 --> 35:48.890
PAMELA: It can.

35:50.482 --> 35:52.519
It can mean everything,
if you let it.

35:52.609 --> 35:53.941
(SOBBING) Oh, God.

35:54.861 --> 35:57.148
Stop, Serena.
Enough drama!

35:57.238 --> 35:58.570
(SERENA CONTINUES SOBBING)

35:59.866 --> 36:02.984
It's the worst thing in the world
to watch your child in pain.

36:05.413 --> 36:07.746
The worst pain
any mother could bear.

36:09.376 --> 36:10.412
(SNIFFLES)

36:10.960 --> 36:12.371
No, it isn't.

36:15.006 --> 36:16.042
What?

36:16.383 --> 36:18.124
It's not the worst.

36:21.012 --> 36:23.800
It might help you to stop indulging
those feelings.

36:24.516 --> 36:25.552
The self-pity.

36:31.106 --> 36:32.688
You gave
that baby away.

36:33.483 --> 36:34.519
(SERENA
CONTINUES SOBBING)

36:38.947 --> 36:40.404
And it wasn't
even yours.

36:45.495 --> 36:47.282
I'm going to draw you
a hot bath.

36:49.207 --> 36:50.368
A hot bath will help.

36:51.876 --> 36:53.242
(CONTINUES SOBBING)

37:10.270 --> 37:12.978
- (DOG BARKING)
- (SIGHS)

37:15.567 --> 37:16.603
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

37:22.282 --> 37:23.318
Hi.

37:24.659 --> 37:25.695
Hey.

37:28.955 --> 37:30.196
You're not here for me.

37:38.590 --> 37:39.876
(FAINT KNOCKING ON DOOR)

37:49.684 --> 37:50.925
How did this happen?

37:51.853 --> 37:52.969
It was my due.

37:53.730 --> 37:57.474
So you're a Commander now, and you can
go get Hannah. You can get me out.

38:00.111 --> 38:01.192
I'm sorry.

38:01.488 --> 38:03.775
Why? Why can't you?

38:03.865 --> 38:05.481
Is there something wrong
with Lawrence?

38:05.575 --> 38:07.032
Lawrence is
a psychopath.

38:08.495 --> 38:09.611
What do you
know about him?

38:10.205 --> 38:11.205
I don't know anything.

38:11.289 --> 38:12.289
Can you find out?

38:12.791 --> 38:15.124
Not really.
He's too high up.

38:15.210 --> 38:16.496
What can you do?

38:18.379 --> 38:19.836
Can you do anything?

38:20.715 --> 38:22.297
What are you good for?

38:23.885 --> 38:25.296
I'm getting deployed.

38:27.096 --> 38:28.096
To the front.

38:29.891 --> 38:30.891
Chicago.

38:34.145 --> 38:35.477
You'll get killed.

38:37.148 --> 38:38.810
I wanted to say goodbye.

38:41.528 --> 38:42.564
Goodbye.

38:57.752 --> 38:59.493
(DOOR OPENS)

39:01.339 --> 39:02.455
(DOOR CLOSES)

39:56.519 --> 39:57.555
(DOOR LOCKS)

40:02.817 --> 40:04.417
SIENNA: You have a visitor
in the parlor.

40:23.963 --> 40:24.963
(EXHALES)

40:43.983 --> 40:45.394
Blessed be the fruit.

40:46.945 --> 40:47.981
Hi.

40:56.829 --> 40:57.865
(DOOR CLOSES)

40:58.164 --> 40:59.200
How are you?

41:02.001 --> 41:03.082
Serena?

41:07.423 --> 41:08.959
Do you think about her?

41:16.224 --> 41:17.340
Every minute.

41:22.188 --> 41:23.599
How do you stop?

41:33.324 --> 41:34.485
(SIGHS)

41:48.881 --> 41:49.997
(SERENA SNIFFLES)

41:50.425 --> 41:51.882
How do you remember her?

41:54.554 --> 41:55.590
How do you see her?

41:58.599 --> 41:59.760
In the bath.

42:02.020 --> 42:03.136
(LAUGHS TEARFULLY)

42:04.022 --> 42:05.433
She loved the water.

42:05.940 --> 42:07.021
(CHUCKLES)

42:08.568 --> 42:09.979
She's gonna be
a swimmer.

42:12.488 --> 42:14.445
Remember how she used
to raise her hand?

42:18.119 --> 42:19.735
It's like she had
a point to make.

42:21.497 --> 42:23.159
That's the
politician in her.

42:25.752 --> 42:28.119
I think she gets
that from you.

42:31.799 --> 42:33.381
She isn't mine.

42:35.386 --> 42:36.547
Serena,

42:39.432 --> 42:41.845
only a mother could do
what you did.

42:48.357 --> 42:50.064
If you can just think...

42:53.446 --> 42:56.780
If you can just think about
all the other mothers

42:58.493 --> 42:59.574
who have...

43:03.122 --> 43:05.705
Who have had their children
taken away from them.

43:10.713 --> 43:11.794
Like you.

43:16.969 --> 43:19.177
There has to be
something we can do.

43:20.515 --> 43:21.515
(SNIFFLES)

43:23.142 --> 43:24.724
That isn't
why I came here.

43:25.394 --> 43:26.760
We can help each other.

43:28.439 --> 43:29.850
We cannot count on them.

43:32.985 --> 43:34.351
They hate us, Serena.

43:38.157 --> 43:39.989
They are not on our side.

43:42.703 --> 43:43.819
I tried.

43:44.122 --> 43:46.034
You have to try harder.

43:47.542 --> 43:49.158
I'm not that
person anymore.

43:50.211 --> 43:51.622
You're scared.

43:55.675 --> 43:56.836
Use it.

44:08.062 --> 44:10.725
Maybe we're stronger than
we think we are.

44:59.113 --> 45:00.570
I made my choices.

45:03.451 --> 45:06.239
OFJOSEPH: <i>There was a time
when women were able to choose.</i>

45:09.832 --> 45:14.327
<i>"We were a society dying," Aunt Lydia
would say, "of too much choice.</i>

45:15.421 --> 45:19.040
<i>"We know the sacrifices you are
expected to make," she'd say.</i>

45:19.842 --> 45:21.834
<i>"It is hard
when men revile you."</i>

45:55.294 --> 45:57.786
We have five new Marthas
for the resistance.

45:58.214 --> 46:03.005
An engineer, an IT tech,
a journalist, a lawyer, and a thief.

46:03.636 --> 46:04.717
BETH: How do you know?

46:05.763 --> 46:07.095
I chose them.

46:13.229 --> 46:15.346
Upstairs now.
Eleanor's sheets need changing.

46:18.567 --> 46:19.728
OFJOSEPH: Hey, Sienna.

46:23.489 --> 46:24.980
We survived another day.

46:36.836 --> 46:42.377
OFJOSEPH: <i>Mother, I think, wherever
you may be, can you hear me?</i>

46:46.137 --> 46:47.924
<i>You wanted
a women's culture.</i>

46:48.681 --> 46:51.219
<i>Well, now there is one.</i>

46:52.268 --> 46:53.429
<i>It isn't what you meant,</i>

46:54.103 --> 46:55.435
<i>but it exists.</i>

47:34.852 --> 47:36.593
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

47:42.818 --> 47:44.229
<i>And here's what we do.</i>

47:45.613 --> 47:48.321
<i>We watch them. The men.</i>

47:49.116 --> 47:51.824
<i>We study them.
We feed them.</i>

47:52.703 --> 47:53.819
<i>We please them.</i>

47:55.539 --> 47:57.121
<i>We can make them
feel strong</i>

47:58.209 --> 48:01.919
<i>or weak.
We know them that well.</i>

48:03.506 --> 48:05.213
<i>We know their
worst nightmares.</i>

48:08.677 --> 48:12.546
<i>And, with a bit of practice,
that's what we'll become.</i>

48:13.808 --> 48:14.969
<i>Nightmares.</i>

48:16.102 --> 48:18.765
<i>One day, when we're ready,</i>

48:19.730 --> 48:21.312
<i>we are coming for you.</i>

48:23.651 --> 48:24.651
<i>Just wait.</i>

48:30.366 --> 48:33.234
(WAVES SPLASHING)

48:40.626 --> 48:43.835
(SEAGULLS SQUAWKING)

